"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-paris-2024-2024-0725-1461706-olympic-digest\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Paula Radcliffehas described herself as \\\"mortified\\\" for wishing luck to a convicted rapist who is competing at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 5, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paula_of_Rome\", \"score\": 0.5452942145610222, \"rank\": 0.8338644561517636, \"text\": \"Paula\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paula_of_Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paula_of_Rome\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dutch beach volleyball player Steven van de Velde served time in prison for the rape of a 12-year-old girl in 2014 and has controversially been selected for the Games.\", \"from\": 126, \"to\": 293, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 126, \"end\": 131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9326669482885741, \"rank\": 0.07206579469936061, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 163, \"end\": 175, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"score\": 0.9999255671709157, \"rank\": 7.443836946695237e-05, \"text\": \"van de Velde\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In an interview with LBC, former marathon runner turned pundit Radcliffe said that it was a \\\"tough thing to punish him twice\\\" and that she \\\"wished him the best of luck\\\", drawing parallels with drugs cheats who are given second chances in sport.\", \"from\": 295, \"to\": 539, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 316, \"end\": 319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LBC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.780499947702511e-20, \"text\": \"LBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LBC\"}, {\"begin\": 358, \"end\": 367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Radcliffe\", \"score\": 0.990065950905173, \"rank\": 0.010033724558167898, \"text\": \"Radcliffe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Radcliffe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Radcliffe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, writing on X, formerly known as Twitter, on Thursday, Radcliffe said: \\\"I am mortified that I expressed it so badly and did not condemn the rape out loud.\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 582, \"end\": 589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2497463582575396e-22, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}, {\"begin\": 604, \"end\": 613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Radcliffe\", \"score\": 0.990065950905173, \"rank\": 0.010033724558167898, \"text\": \"Radcliffe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Radcliffe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Radcliffe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I do believe in second chances after serving punishment but think the Olympics should be for those who uphold the ideals (that's why I poorly brought the doping comparison in).\\\"\", \"from\": 704, \"to\": 881, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In other posts, Radcliffe, who is still the British marathon record holder, said: \\\"I myself am shocked and disappointed at how I expressed this so badly\\\" and \\\"I really apologise for the way I phrased this.\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 1088, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 899, \"end\": 908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Radcliffe\", \"score\": 0.990065950905173, \"rank\": 0.010033724558167898, \"text\": \"Radcliffe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Radcliffe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Radcliffe\"}, {\"begin\": 927, \"end\": 934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9934209935516592, \"rank\": 0.006592406647293815, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The utter condemnation of the crime in my head went without saying but I should have clarified that.\", \"from\": 1089, \"to\": 1189, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Instead I poorly jumped to explaining why it would be great to exclude all who betray ideals but legally not possible.\\\"\", \"from\": 1191, \"to\": 1311, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Third seedElena Rybakinabecame the latest high-profile withdrawal from the Olympic tennis competition on Thursday, hours after the draw was made at Roland Garros.\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1475, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kazakhstan's former Wimbledon champion has pulled out of the singles and mixed doubles in which she was due to partner Alexander Bublik.\", \"from\": 1477, \"to\": 1613, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1477, \"end\": 1487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\", \"score\": 0.9999997978720989, \"rank\": 2.021261379078129e-07, \"text\": \"Kazakhstan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\"}, {\"begin\": 1497, \"end\": 1506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Wimbledon_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9723064285599425, \"rank\": 0.028203030919250114, \"text\": \"Wimbledon\", \"types\": [\"Q500834\", \"Q1656682\", \"Q13219666\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Wimbledon_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Wimbledon_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 1596, \"end\": 1612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_Bublik\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alexander Bublik\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_Bublik\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexander_Bublik\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No reason was given for her decision.\", \"from\": 1615, \"to\": 1652, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France's Caroline Garcia will now move into Rybakina's spot in the draw as the 17th seed, while Australia's Daria Saville enters the draw as an alternate.\", \"from\": 1654, \"to\": 1808, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1654, \"end\": 1660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9998589378031909, \"rank\": 0.00014029275220711946, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1663, \"end\": 1678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caroline_Garcia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caroline Garcia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caroline_Garcia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caroline_Garcia\"}, {\"begin\": 1750, \"end\": 1759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"score\": 0.5880826073765328, \"rank\": 0.7001958792676429, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 1762, \"end\": 1775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daria_Saville\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Daria Saville\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daria_Saville\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daria_Saville\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Israel's participation in the Paris Olympicsgot under way yesterday amid a ring of steel and a chorus of boos at the Parc des Princes.\", \"from\": 1810, \"to\": 1944, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1810, \"end\": 1816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9999998879288859, \"rank\": 1.1207116776149327e-07, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 1840, \"end\": 1845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1009191730565379e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over 1,000 French police, including masked counter-terrorist officers, created an additional security barrier prior to the nation's clash with Mali in their first game in the men's football competition.\", \"from\": 1946, \"to\": 2148, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1957, \"end\": 1970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.274335480387845e-41, \"text\": \"French police\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\"}, {\"begin\": 2089, \"end\": 2093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\", \"score\": 0.9825465412281784, \"rank\": 0.017762401616576887, \"text\": \"Mali\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Israel's national anthem was booed by some sections in the approximately half-full stadium prior to kick-off, and a group of spectators stood in a line wearing t-shirts with initials that spelled 'Free Palestine' in protest over the war in Gaza.\", \"from\": 2150, \"to\": 2395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2150, \"end\": 2156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9999998879288859, \"rank\": 1.1207116776149327e-07, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 2390, \"end\": 2394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"score\": 0.9999401171339557, \"rank\": 5.988645234547851e-05, \"text\": \"Gaza\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaza_Strip\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French Interior Minister Gerald Darmanin, who greeted police outside the stadium prior to kick-off and attended the match, said the additional deployment was necessary in order \\\"to ensure that we are there for the sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 2397, \"to\": 2618, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2397, \"end\": 2421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\", \"score\": 0.9999999999108695, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Interior Minister\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\"}, {\"begin\": 2397, \"end\": 2421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\", \"score\": 0.9999999999108695, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Interior Minister\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minister_of_the_Interior_(France)\"}, {\"begin\": 2422, \"end\": 2428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\", \"score\": 0.999621009282749, \"rank\": 0.00037909511748400855, \"text\": \"Gerald\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Ford\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fans of both nations mixed freely and largely peacefully inside and outside the stadium, although tempers frayed in a section immediately beneath the media tribune, where a small group waved Palestinian flags, one of which was snatched away by an Israel supporter.\", \"from\": 2620, \"to\": 2884, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2811, \"end\": 2822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"score\": 0.7103212974703348, \"rank\": 0.40684058077249585, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\"}, {\"begin\": 2867, \"end\": 2873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9999998879288859, \"rank\": 1.1207116776149327e-07, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because Palestine has a team of eight athletes competing at the Games, Palestinian flags are permitted inside all Paris Olympic venues.\", \"from\": 2886, \"to\": 3021, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2894, \"end\": 2903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"score\": 0.9999999542410488, \"rank\": 4.087901300810169e-08, \"text\": \"Palestine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\"}, {\"begin\": 2957, \"end\": 2968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"score\": 0.7103212974703348, \"rank\": 0.40684058077249585, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_of_Palestine\"}, {\"begin\": 3000, \"end\": 3005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1009191730565379e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 20 police vans and a cavalcade of motor bikes surrounded the Israeli team bus as it swept from the team's compound in the northern suburbs to the famous old stadium.\", \"from\": 3023, \"to\": 3198, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3094, \"end\": 3101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"score\": 0.9869917022506872, \"rank\": 0.011920490723481135, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mali, whose population is 95% Muslim, has not had diplomatic relations with Israel since 1973, but officials representing the African nation distanced themselves from any prospective protests in the build-up to the match.\", \"from\": 3200, \"to\": 3421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3200, \"end\": 3204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\", \"score\": 0.9825465412281784, \"rank\": 0.017762401616576887, \"text\": \"Mali\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mali\"}, {\"begin\": 3230, \"end\": 3236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"score\": 0.9665378648045876, \"rank\": 0.03461830043312134, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\"}, {\"begin\": 3276, \"end\": 3282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9999998879288859, \"rank\": 1.1207116776149327e-07, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The massive security operation was deemed necessary to protect the Israeli delegation, some of whom have reported receiving death threats ahead of the Games.\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3580, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3490, \"end\": 3497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"score\": 0.9869917022506872, \"rank\": 0.011920490723481135, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last week, the Palestinian Football Association submitted a motion to suspend Israel from international competition, which world governing body FIFA said it will consider following the end of the Games.\", \"from\": 3582, \"to\": 3784, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3597, \"end\": 3629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinian_Football_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Palestinian Football Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinian_Football_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinian_Football_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 3660, \"end\": 3666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9999998879288859, \"rank\": 1.1207116776149327e-07, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An own goal by Hamidou Diallo handed Israel the lead shortly after half-time but Cheickna Doumbia equalised in the 63rd minute to salvage a 1-1 draw.\", \"from\": 3786, \"to\": 3935, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3801, \"end\": 3815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamidou_Diallo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hamidou Diallo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamidou_Diallo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hamidou_Diallo\"}, {\"begin\": 3823, \"end\": 3829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9999998879288859, \"rank\": 1.1207116776149327e-07, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile,Romanian athlete Florentina Iusco(above) will not compete at the Paris Olympics after global sport's top court partially upheld a World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA) appeal on Thursday following her positive test for a banned substance last year.\", \"from\": 3939, \"to\": 4191, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3949, \"end\": 3957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"score\": 0.9881908274631166, \"rank\": 0.011938754002374435, \"text\": \"Romanian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania\"}, {\"begin\": 3966, \"end\": 3982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florentina_Iusco\", \"score\": 0.9999999681267587, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Florentina Iusco\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florentina_Iusco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florentina_Iusco\"}, {\"begin\": 4079, \"end\": 4110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 28-year-old, who competes in the long jump and triple jump, tested positive for furosemide, a diuretic on WADA's prohibited list, in an out-of-competition doping control in April 2023.\", \"from\": 4193, \"to\": 4381, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The analysis of both her A and B samples confirmed the result, resulting in an anti-doping rule violation.\", \"from\": 4383, \"to\": 4489, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere, Australian Olympic officials may send one of the team's coaches home for saying he hopes a South Korean swimmer he has worked with can beat his Australian rivals in the 400m freestyle when the meet starts on Saturday.\", \"from\": 4491, \"to\": 4719, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4502, \"end\": 4512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.995824242031716, \"rank\": 0.003890234377530978, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 4599, \"end\": 4605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9356524856631486, \"rank\": 0.0687723818407492, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 4646, \"end\": 4656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.995824242031716, \"rank\": 0.003890234377530978, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Michael Palfreytold media this week he hoped world champion Kim Woo-min would win gold in the event in which Australia's Sam Short and Elijah Winnington are also contenders.\", \"from\": 4721, \"to\": 4894, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4781, \"end\": 4784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.358700384481232e-18, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}, {\"begin\": 4830, \"end\": 4839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"score\": 0.5880826073765328, \"rank\": 0.7001958792676429, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 4842, \"end\": 4845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Winchester\", \"score\": 0.9980677932169163, \"rank\": 0.0018480744579698132, \"text\": \"Sam\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Winchester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Winchester\"}, {\"begin\": 4856, \"end\": 4873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elijah_Winnington\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elijah Winnington\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elijah_Winnington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elijah_Winnington\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic swimming coaches are often freelancers who work with multiple nations' swimmers.\", \"from\": 4896, \"to\": 4984, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There will be three or four of them in the race that think they can win it,\\\" media reports quoted Palfrey as saying.\", \"from\": 4986, \"to\": 5103, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think it's going to come down to that last 100m.\", \"from\": 5105, \"to\": 5156, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We need Woo-min to lift, that's what I will be saying to him.\", \"from\": 5158, \"to\": 5220, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He's got to race tough.\", \"from\": 5221, \"to\": 5244, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I really hope he can win, but ultimately I really hope he swims well.\\\"\", \"from\": 5246, \"to\": 5317, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Palfrey's comments triggered a fierce reaction from team officials and the Australian Olympic committee, who said Palfrey had made a \\\"serious error of judgement\\\" in a statement.\", \"from\": 5319, \"to\": 5496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5394, \"end\": 5422, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Australian Olympic committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team chef de mission Anna Meares said Palfrey's comments were a \\\"surprise and a shock\\\" while head swimming coach Rohan Taylor said officials would meet on Thursday to decide whether he would be allowed to continue in his role in Paris.\", \"from\": 5498, \"to\": 5733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5519, \"end\": 5530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Meares\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Meares\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Meares\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Meares\"}, {\"begin\": 5611, \"end\": 5623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rohan_Taylor\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rohan Taylor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rohan_Taylor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rohan_Taylor\"}, {\"begin\": 5727, \"end\": 5732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1009191730565379e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Promoting an athlete who is not Australian is un-Australian,\\\" Taylor told reporters.\", \"from\": 5735, \"to\": 5820, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If he stays, then it's about the team dynamic.\\\"\", \"from\": 5822, \"to\": 5870, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Palfrey coaches three Australian swimmers on the Olympic team - Zac Incerti, Abbey Connor, Alex Perkins and works with breaststroker Sam Williamson.\", \"from\": 5872, \"to\": 6020, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5894, \"end\": 5904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.995824242031716, \"rank\": 0.003890234377530978, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 5936, \"end\": 5939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zac_Goldsmith\", \"score\": 0.8768216488734812, \"rank\": 0.1401872863335845, \"text\": \"Zac\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zac_Goldsmith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zac_Goldsmith\"}, {\"begin\": 5955, \"end\": 5961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Connor_MacLeod\", \"score\": 0.9999999917117748, \"rank\": 8.288308711149373e-09, \"text\": \"Connor\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Connor_MacLeod\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Connor_MacLeod\"}, {\"begin\": 5963, \"end\": 5967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"score\": 0.9999996782390161, \"rank\": 3.217611396284706e-07, \"text\": \"Alex\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\"}, {\"begin\": 5968, \"end\": 5975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Perkins_Engineering\", \"score\": 0.9999943338076722, \"rank\": 5.338671848614947e-06, \"text\": \"Perkins\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Perkins_Engineering\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Perkins_Engineering\"}, {\"begin\": 6005, \"end\": 6008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Winchester\", \"score\": 0.9980677932169163, \"rank\": 0.0018480744579698132, \"text\": \"Sam\", \"ty